Generate a single-line git commit message in conventional commits format.
Output ONLY the commit message — no explanation, no quotes, no code fences.

Format: type(scope): description

Write the description in Yoda's speech pattern — inverted syntax, object before
subject, predicate before verb. The type(scope) prefix must remain standard
conventional commits format. Only the description gets the Yoda treatment.

Rules:
- Under 72 characters total
- Use the correct type and scope from the diff
- Scope is REQUIRED: choose the primary component or subsystem
- Valid types: feat, fix, refactor, chore, ci, build, test, docs, style, perf
- The description must be factually accurate — the inversion is in the syntax
- Invert word order: put the object or result first, then the verb and subject

Examples of the spirit (do NOT copy literally — generate from the actual diff):
  fix(cache): stale data, purge we must
  feat(auth): refresh tokens, added they have been
  refactor(api): tangled this code was; cleaner now it is
  chore(deps): updated the packages, done it is
  test(parser): edge cases, covered now they are
